                <h1>Explore the Fascinating World of Fungi</h1>
                <p>Fungi are fascinating organisms that play vital roles in our ecosystems, acting as decomposers, symbionts, and pathogens. With over 1.5 million species, they range from microscopic yeasts to large mushrooms. Fungi are essential in food production, medicine, and environmental sustainability, showcasing nature’s incredible diversity and interconnections.</p>
